\section1 The Layout Menu 

This menu is invoked with \Key Alt+L, and provides the following
options:
\list 

\i \Menu {Layout|Adjust Size} Click this menu option (or press \Key
Ctrl+J) to adjust the size of the widget to it's recommended size. 

\i \Menu {Layout|Lay Out Horizontally} Click this menu option (or
press \Key Ctrl+H) to lay out the selected widgets or layouts side by
side. Use \Key Shift+Click to select each widget or layout, and then
choose this menu option to group them horizontally. Note that for
complex widgets it is sometimes easiest to select widgets and layouts
by clicking them in the Widgets tab of the \l{Object Explorer} window.

\i \Menu {Layout|Lay Out Vertically} Click this menu option (or press
\Key Ctrl+L) to lay out the selected widgets one above the other. Use
\Key Shift+Click to select each widget or layout, and then choose this
menu option to group them vertically. Note that for complex widgets it
is sometimes easiest to select widgets and layouts by clicking them in
the Widgets tab of the \l{Object Explorer} window.

\i \Menu {Layout|Lay Out in a Grid} Click this menu option (or press
\Key Ctrl+G) 

\i \Menu {Layout|Lay Out Horizontally (in Splitter)} Click this menu
option to lay out the selected widgets or layouts side by
side with a splitter between each widget. Use \Key Shift+Click to
select each widget or layout, and then choose this menu option to group
them horizontally. Note that for complex widgets it is sometimes
easiest to select widgets and layouts by clicking them in the Widgets
tab of the \l{Object Explorer} window.

\i \Menu {Layout|Lay Out Vertically (in Splitter)} Click this menu
option to lay out the selected widgets or layouts one above the other
with a splitter between each widget or layout. Use \Key{Shift+Click} to
select each widget or layout, and then choose this menu option to
group them vertically. Note that for complex widgets it is sometimes
easiest to select widgets and layouts by clicking them in the Widgets
tab of the \l{Object Explorer} window.

\i \Menu {Layout|Break Layout} Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+B) to break apart layouts that have been created. Click on the layout and select this option; the layouts are then seperated. 

\i \Menu {Layout|Add Spacer} Click this menu option to add a spacer
to widgets that take up too much space on the form. The spacer consumes extra space in the layout.

\endlist

See also the \l{The Layout Toolbar buttons}.

