\section1 The Window Menu

This menu is invoked with \Key Alt+W, and provides the following
options:
\list 

\i \Menu{Window|Close} Click this menu option (or press \Key
Ctrl+F4) to close the window that is currently active.

\i \Menu{Window|Close All} Click this menu option to close all the
windows that are currently open.

\i \Menu{Window|Next} Click this menu option (or press \Key Ctrl+F6) to
view each window in the order in which they were opened, continuing on
to the next window that was opened.

\i \Menu{Window|Previous} Click this menu option (or press \Key
Ctrl+Shift+F6) to view each window in reverse order from last window that you opened. 

\i \Menu{Window|Tile} Click this menu option to arrange allthe open
files and forms side by side so that each window is visible. This
option provides a way to organize the windows so that each open window
is equally visible and easier to view.

\i \Menu{Window|Cascade} Click this menu option to stack all the
open file and forms, one on top of the other. This option provides an
easier way to organize and view all the windows that are opened.

\i \Menu{Window|Views|Output Window} Click this menu option to invoke
the \l{Output Window}, which provides features used for debugging
code.

\i \Menu{Window|Views|File Overview} Click this menu option to make
the \l{File Overview} window visible or to hide the window if you do not
want it to be visible. 

\i \Menu{Window|Views|Property Editors/Signal Handlers} Click this
menu option to make the \l{Property Editors/Signal Handlers} window
visible or to hide the window if you do not want it to be visible. 

\i \Menu{Window|Views|Object Explorer} Click this menu option to make
the \l{Object Explorer} window visible or to hide the window if you do not want it to be visible. 

\i \Menu{Window|Views|Line Up} Click this menu option to eliminate
extra space between toolbars and line them up next to each other all
at once, rather than moving each individual toolbar into place.

\i \Menu{Window|Toolbars|File} Click this menu option to make the File
toolbar buttons visible or to hide the toolbar buttons if you do not
want them to be visible. If the toolbar buttons are currently visible,
a check mark will appear next to the name in the menu. 

\i \Menu{Window|Toolbars|Edit} Click this menu option to make the Edit
toolbar buttons visible or to hide the toolbar buttons if you do not want them to be visible. If the toolbar buttons are currently visible, a check mark will appear next to the name in the menu. 

\i \Menu{Window|Toolbars|Search} Click this menu option to make the
